description:
'''Sambass''', '''drum 'n' bossa''' or '''drum 'n' sambass''' (a [[portmanteau]] of "[[samba]]" and "[[Bass (sound)|bass]]") is a regional subgenre of [[drum and bass]] music mostly native to [[Brazil]], which combines drum and bass rhythms with influences from [[Latin American music]].

Popular artists in the genre include [[DJ Marky]], [[DJ Patife]], [[XRS Land]], [[Drumagick]], [[Marcelinho da Lua]], [[Kaleidoscopio]] and DJ Roots.  Four compilation albums titles ''Sambass Vol. 1'' through ''Sambass Vol. 4'' were released to international acclaim, by the Italian record label Cuadra.
